5:
A group of kidnappers? And you
want Stella and I to expose them?
9:
They're after upper-class organic
women and have already captured
a number of victims.
11:
Though ransoms have been paid,
they sell the victims to other people.
They're a highly unsavory sort.
16:
So why are you asking for our help
and not Bulleta's?
20:
She's too well known for an
undercover op like this. I thought of
handling the situation myself at first,
but...
25: No. You can't charge in alone.
29:
Right. Well, that's why I'm asking for
your assistance. I hate to drag Stella
into danger like this...
33:
But you have nothing to fear. I've
already made arrangements to
ensure your success.
36:
You might be a little surprised at
first, but I'm sure you'll be satisfied
with what I have planned.
42: I think they're gone now. Stella?
46: Of course. Show me your handcuffs.
51:
And just like that, they're off. Love's
master keycode really is something...
54:
And now we just need to wait for our
rescue to arri—
61:
All right, the prisoners aren't dead.
Doing good so far!
70:
Sure am! I'm here to bust you outta
here!
72:
Looks like you managed pretty well
on your own, huh? You can leave the
rest to me!
76:
Oh, um, Strina? We've got the
master keycode right here—
82:
Heh! Just sit back and watch me
work!
87:
Hope you two stretched earlier,
'cause it's time for our grand escape!
102:
Hah! Their first mistake was
underestimating an ex-engineer!
109:
Hold it right there! You're not getting
out of here that easily!
112:
Oh. Someone finally noticed my
signal-jamming, huh?
115:
You really thought you could trash
our base and make it out alive? Like
hell!
119:
Pssh. What did I just say like three
seconds ago?
125:
Oops! They listen to me now. Tough
break, dumbass!
146:
Anyway, let's head out before we get
buried alive, okay?
161:
Go ahead, Strina! We'll be right
behind you!
168: Heh, hold up! I'm coming too!
176:
So it turns out that cat was some big
wig's pet. Looks like it was missing,
but it's back with its owner now.
182:
I'm just glad the cat is safe at home
now.
185: Thanks for all your help, Strina.
189:
No prob! It's been a while since I got
a chance to cut loose like that!
191:
Besides, I got a huge payout! And it's
all thanks to you!
200:
DayAndNight's been on the decline
recently, so I haven't gotten a
request from them in a while.
202:
But once I show up for the job, I find
organic troubleshooters who can
actually hold their own. You even
know what cats are!
206:
...I guess you wouldn't see too many
cats around here, huh.
209: Why do you want to know about us?
216:
It's fun to take things apart and see
what makes 'em tick, right? It's the
same with people!
219:
Besides, you two are just adorbs.
Nothing weird about that, right?
235:
A natural sky, eh? Even prettier than
I expected.
239:
I don't know if "natural" is the right
word, but...
247: Sure is! I love it here!
251:
If you're going to work with us, we'll
cook meals using natural
ingredients for you.
256:
Seriously? This beats the hell out of
my old job!
259:
Call me whenever you need my help
with something, all right?
262:
Nobody's feeling any work stress as
long as I'm around!
